Next, update the `login()` method in the `LoginActivity` to retrieve the <Tooltip tip="ID Token: Credential meant for the client itself, rather than for accessing a resource." cta="View Glossary" href="/docs/glossary?term=ID+Token">ID Token</Tooltip> and get the user profile from the token with the JWTDecode.Android library. Then store the user profile with the `UserProfileManager`.

```java lines
// ...
@Override
public void onSuccess(@NonNull final Credentials credentials) {
    runOnUiThread(new Runnable() {
        @Override
        public void run() {
            Toast.makeText(LoginActivity.this, "Log In - Success", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT).show();
        }
    });

    credentialsManager.saveCredentials(credentials);
    JWT jwt = new JWT(credentials.getIdToken());
    User user = new User(
            jwt.getClaim("email").asString(),
            jwt.getClaim("name").asString(),
            jwt.getClaim("picture").asString()
    );
    UserProfileManager.saveUserInfo(LoginActivity.this, user);

    startActivity(new Intent(LoginActivity.this, TimeSheetActivity.class));
}
